---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'May 13, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Notice of Privacy Practices · Viva Wellness Co."
  description="Summary of how Viva Wellness Co. uses and discloses protected health information (PHI), and your rights as a patient under HIPAA and Texas, Colorado, and Florida law."
>

  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container legal-hero__inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">· HIPAA Notice</span>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title">
        Notice of <span class="italic-display">privacy practices.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Required by HIPAA for any practice that handles protected health
        information. This is the public-facing summary. Patients receive the
        full notice at intake, which they sign acknowledging receipt.
      </p>
      <p class="legal-hero__updated">Effective · {lastUpdated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-body">
    <div class="container legal-body__inner">

      <div class="legal-callout">
        <strong>Important.</strong>
        This notice describes how protected health information (PHI) about
        you may be used and disclosed, and how you can get access to this
        information. Please review carefully. The full notice with all
        required disclosures is provided in your patient portal at
        enrollment and re-issued whenever it materially changes.
      </div>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Who this notice applies to</h2>
      <p>
        This Notice applies to Viva Wellness Co. and the licensed providers
        practicing under it. It describes how we may use and disclose
        <strong>protected health information</strong> (PHI) about our
        patients and how a patient can access this information.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most patient interaction with PHI happens inside our HIPAA-compliant
        patient portal (Charm Health). This website (vivawellnessco.com) is a
        marketing site and does not collect or store PHI. See our
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for what this website does
        collect.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">How we may use and disclose PHI</h2>
      <p>We use and disclose PHI for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Treatment.</strong> To provide, coordinate, or manage your
          health care. For example, your provider will review your labs and
          history to determine an appropriate protocol.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Payment.</strong> To bill for services and obtain payment.
          We may share PHI with our payment processor (GlossGenius) or your
          insurance carrier when applicable.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Health-care operations.</strong> Internal quality review,
          training, and management of the practice. We do not use PHI for
          marketing without your written authorization.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Required by law.</strong> When federal, state, or local law
          requires disclosure (subpoena, public-health reporting, etc.).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>To protect health and safety.</strong> When disclosure is
          necessary to prevent or lessen a serious threat.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Business associates.</strong> Vendors who handle PHI on our
          behalf under signed Business Associate Agreements (e.g. the
          patient-portal platform, the compounding pharmacies that fill
          prescriptions, the lab company that runs your blood draw).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Any use or disclosure of PHI not listed above will be made only with
        your written authorization. You may revoke that authorization in
        writing at any time, except where we have already acted in reliance
        on it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">What we will NOT do without your authorization</h2>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>Sell your PHI</li>
        <li>Use your PHI for marketing communications (other than appointment reminders or treatment-related messages)</li>
        <li>Use your PHI for fundraising</li>
        <li>Share psychotherapy notes</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Your rights regarding your PHI</h2>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Right to inspect and copy.</strong> Request access to your
          patient record. We provide it within thirty days. A reasonable
          cost-based fee may apply for paper copies.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to amend.</strong> Ask us to correct PHI you believe
          is incomplete or inaccurate. We have sixty days to respond and
          may deny in specific circumstances (you can appeal).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to an accounting of disclosures.</strong> Receive a
          list of certain disclosures of your PHI made by us in the last six
          years.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to request restrictions.</strong> Ask us to limit how
          we use or disclose your PHI. We will try to honor reasonable
          requests; we are required to honor a request to restrict
          disclosure to a health plan if the service is paid in full
          out-of-pocket.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to confidential communications.</strong> Request that
          we contact you in a specific way (e.g. only by text, only at a
          specific phone number) or at a specific location.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to a paper copy of this notice</strong> upon request,
          even if you originally received it electronically.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Right to be notified of a breach</strong> of unsecured PHI.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Our duties</h2>
      <p>
        We are required by law to maintain the privacy of PHI, provide you
        with this Notice, abide by its terms while it is in effect, and
        notify you within sixty days of discovery if a breach of your
        unsecured PHI occurs, as required by the HIPAA Breach Notification
        Rule (45 CFR &sect; 164.404).
      </p>
      <p>
        We may change the terms of this Notice. Material changes will be
        posted in your patient portal and on this page with a new effective
        date. Updated terms apply to PHI we maintain, including PHI
        collected before the update.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">How to exercise your rights or file a complaint</h2>
      <p>
        To exercise any of these rights, email
        <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
        or send a written request to the address below. We may ask you to
        verify your identity before fulfilling requests.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you believe your privacy rights have been violated, you may file
        a complaint with:
      </p>
      <ul class="legal-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Viva Wellness Co.</strong> Email
          <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
          or write to the address below.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>U.S. Department of Health and Human Services, Office for
          Civil Rights.</strong>
          <a href="https://www.hhs.gov/ocr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hhs.gov/ocr</a>
          · (800) 368-1019 · TDD: (800) 537-7697 · Email
          <a href="mailto:OCRComplaint@hhs.gov">OCRComplaint@hhs.gov</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You will not be retaliated against in any way for filing a complaint.
      </p>

      <h2 class="legal-h">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:info&#64;vivawellnessco.com">info&#64;vivawellnessco.com</a>
        or call <a href="tel:+17372107283">(737) 210-7283</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="legal-foot">
        Viva Wellness Co. · 5900 Balcones Dr #19640, Austin, TX 78731 ·
        Effective {lastUpdated}
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    padding: clamp(5rem, 11vw, 9rem) 0 clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .legal-hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: radial-gradient(800px 500px at 75% 0%, rgba(214, 134, 74, 0.14), transparent 65%);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .legal-hero__inner { position: relative; max-width: 70ch; }
  .legal-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.6rem, 6.5vw, 5rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-hero__title .italic-display { color: var(--bronze-bright); }
  .legal-hero__updated {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--mute);
    margin-top: 1.4rem;
    padding-top: 1.2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    display: inline-block;
  }

  .legal-body { padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) 0 clamp(5rem, 10vw, 8rem); }
  .legal-body__inner { max-width: 70ch; margin: 0 auto; }

  .legal-callout {
    background: var(--ink-2);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--bronze);
    padding: 1.6rem 1.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(247, 244, 238, 0.9);
  }
  .legal-callout strong {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--bronze);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
  }

  .legal-h {
    font-family: var(--font-display-italic);
    font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.6vw, 1.9rem);
    line-height: 1.2;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    margin: 2.8rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--paper);
  }
  .legal-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(247, 244, 238, 0.85);
    margin-bottom: 1.1rem;
    max-width: none;
  }
  .legal-body a {
    color: var(--bronze);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(214, 134, 74, 0.4);
    transition: color 200ms var(--ease), border-color 200ms var(--ease);
  }
  .legal-body a:hover {
    color: var(--bronze-bright);
    border-color: var(--bronze-bright);
  }
  .legal-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    margin: 0.5rem 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .legal-list li {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    position: relative;
    color: rgba(247, 244, 238, 0.85);
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .legal-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--bronze);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .legal-list strong { color: var(--paper); }

  .legal-foot {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--mute);
  }
</style>
